w":0.15}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Raw model output is captured to a diagnostic artifact before any JSON parsing or extraction logic runs.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is pipeline ordering across model-call wrapper, artifact writer, and parser modules. Real model not required; deterministic stub output can verify ordering. Candidate tests: Integration candidate: inject malformed raw output, assert artifact exists with raw payload before parser error; catches ordering bug. Unit candidate on parser alone cannot verify pre-parse capture side effect. Rejection gate: Agentic rejected because behavior is instrumentation order, not model output quality.","test_description":"Run harness path with a controlled model response that breaks parsing; assert diagnostic artifact contains exact raw response and timestamp/event ordering indicates capture occurred before parse/extract step.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Assertions enforce structural behavior constraints (for example schema paths and role-specific field placement), not only keyword presence checks.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Primary failure is assertion logic expressiveness (structure vs keyword), which is local and deterministic on provided payloads. Candidate tests: Unit candidate: feed payload with correct keywords but wrong schema path/role placement; assert structural validator fails while keyword checker would pass; catches false-positive risk. Integration candidate adds harness plumbing but does not increase detection of this logic defect. Rejection gate: higher levels disqualified because behavior text is about assertion semantics, not infrastructure or live model dependence.","test_description":"Test assertion module with crafted outputs: one keyword-only false positive and one structurally valid sample